%S A397787 1,0,0,0,1,0,2,1,2,0,4,1,5,0,2,2,7,0,8,2,3,0,10,1,8,0,6,3,13,0,14,4,5,
%T A397787 0,8,2,17,0,6,3,19,0,20,5,6,0,22,2,18,0,8,6,25,0,14,5,9,0,28,1,29,0,
%U A397787 10,8,17,0,32,8,11,0,34,4,35,0,8,9,23,0,38,6,18,0,40,2,23
%N A397787 Number of even primitive Dirichlet characters modulo n.
%H A397787 Jianing Song, <a href="/A397787/b397787.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A397787 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dirichlet_character">Dirichlet character</a>.
%F A397787 Let b(n) = A007431(n) be the number of primitive Dirichlet characters modulo n.
%F A397787 - If b(n) is even (i.e., n == 2 (mod 4) or n is divisible by 8 or an odd prime squared), then a(n) = b(n)/2;
%F A397787 - If b(n) is odd (i.e., n is an odd squarefree number or 4 times an odd squarefree number), then a(n) = (b(n) + (-1)^omega(n))/2.
%F A397787 In other words, if there are an even number of primitive Dirichlet characters modulo n, then half of them are even and half of them are odd; if the number of primitive Dirichlet characters is odd, then the even (resp. odd) characters outnumber by 1 if n has an even (resp. odd) number of distinct prime factors.
%F A397787 These formula can be proved using these relations:
%F A397787 - a(2) = 0, a(4) = 0, a(2^r) = A007431(2^r)/2 = 2^(e-3) for r >= 3;
%F A397787 - For odd primes p, a(p) = (p-3)/2, a(p^r) = A007431(p^r)/2 = (p-1)^2*p^(e-2)/2 for r >= 2;
%F A397787 - a(m*n) = a(m)*a(n) + A397788(m)*A397788(n) if gcd(m,n) = 1.
%e A397787 a(2^r) = 2^(r-3) for r >= 3: Let chi be a generator of the group of characters of 1+4Z/2^rZ (a cyclic group of order 2^(e-2)), then an even primitive character modulo 2^r is an even extension (i.e., taking 1 at -1) of chi^e for odd e.
%e A397787 a(p) = (p-3)/2: Let chi be a generator of the group of characters modulo p (a cyclic group of order p-1), then an odd primitive character modulo p is of the form chi^e for even e !== 0 (mod p-1).
%e A397787 a(p^r) = (p-1)^2*p^(r-2)/2 for odd prime p and r >= 2: Let chi be a generator of the group of characters modulo p^r (a cyclic group of order (p-1)*p^(r-1)), then an even primitive character modulo p is of the form chi^e for even e coprime to p.
%o A397787 (PARI) A397787(n) = my(f=factor(n), w=#f~, num); num=prod(i=1, w, if(f[i, 2]==1, f[i, 1]-2, ((f[i, 1]-1)^2)*(f[i, 1]^(f[i, 2]-2)))); if(num%2==0, num/2, (num+(-1)^w)/2) \\ after _Antti Karttunen_'s program for A007431
%Y A397787 Cf. A007431 (number of all primitive characters), A397788 (number of odd primitive characters), A359591 (excess of even primitive characters over odd ones)..
%K A397787 nonn,easy,new
%O A397787 1,7
%A A397787 _Jianing Song_, Jul 09 2026
